# CloudWatch Alarms

Watches one metric (or metric-math) → **three states**:

- **OK** — within threshold
- **ALARM** — breached per the rules
- **INSUFFICIENT_DATA** — startup, gaps, paused

## Evaluation (the tricky bit)

period **5 min** · **3** eval periods · **2 of 3** datapoints → *ALARM when breached in ≥2 of the last 3 windows*. Too tight → **flaps**; too loose → slow.

## Actions

- **SNS** — email / SMS / Lambda / fan-out (universal)
- **Auto Scaling** — scale an ASG in/out
- **EC2** — stop / terminate / reboot / **recover** (new host, same ID + EBS)

## Variants

- **Composite alarm** — AND/OR of alarms → no alert storms
- **Billing alarm** — `EstimatedCharges`, **us-east-1 only**
